      "title": "See also"
    },
    {
      "blocks": [
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "Logarithm is a multivalued function: for each "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "x"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " there is an infinite\nnumber of "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "z"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " such that "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "exp(z) = x"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": ". The convention is to return the\n"
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "z"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " whose imaginary part lies in "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "(-pi, pi]"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "For real-valued input data types, "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/log",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "log",
              "text": "log"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " always returns real output. For\neach value that cannot be expressed as a real number or infinity, it\nyields "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "nan"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and sets the "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "invalid"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " floating point error flag."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "For complex-valued input, "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/log",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "log",
              "text": "log"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " is a complex analytical function that\nhas a branch cut "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "[-inf, 0]"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": " and is continuous from above on it. "
            },
            {
              "external_url": "",
              "href": "/docs/api/ops/log",
              "kind": "link",
              "target": "log",
              "text": "log"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\nhandles the floating-point negative zero as an infinitesimal negative\nnumber, conforming to the C99 standard."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inline": [
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "In the cases where the input has a negative real part and a very small\nnegative complex part (approaching 0), the result is so close to "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "-pi"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "\nthat it evaluates to exactly "
            },
            {
              "kind": "code",
              "text": "-pi"
            },
            {
              "kind": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
